# 3. ➕ ADD NEW SUBSECTION: “2.7.2 Estimation of α”

### 📍 Place immediately after 2.7.1

---

## Insert:

### (A) Pairwise estimator

```text
For cohorts i and j, define excess hazard:

    e_d(t) = h_obs,d(t) - h_base,d(t)

The pairwise estimator minimizes:

    Σ_{i<j,t} [ log e_i(t) - log e_j(t)
                - (log F_i(t; α) - log F_j(t; α)) ]^2

where F_d(t; α) is the gamma-frailty expectation E[z^α].
```

---

### (B) Collapse estimator

```text
Alternatively, α can be estimated by minimizing cross-cohort variance:

    α̂ = argmin Var_d [ log(e_d(t)) - log F_d(t; α) ]

This estimator enforces consistency of the excess-hazard scaling across cohorts.
```

---

### (C) Practical note

```text
In practice, both estimators yield similar results under adequate signal. Disagreement between estimators is treated as a diagnostic of weak identifiability or model misspecification.
```

